<chapter>
<num>CHAPTER 701—</num>
<heading>DEFINITIONS</heading>
<section>
<num>§ 7001.</num>
<heading> Definitions</heading>
<content>
<p class="indent0">In this title, the term “Army” means the Army or Armies referred to in the Constitution of the United States, less that part established by law as the Air Force.</p>
</content>
<sourceCredit>(<ref>Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041</ref>, <ref>70A Stat. 157</ref>, § 3001; <ref>Pub. L. 100–26, § 7(k)(8)</ref>, <date date="1987-04-21">Apr. 21, 1987</date>, <ref>101 Stat. 284</ref>; renumbered § 7001, <ref>Pub. L. 115–232, div. A, title VIII, § 808(a)</ref>, <date date="2018-08-13">Aug. 13, 2018</date>, <ref>132 Stat. 1838</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
